title: Oxford forestploter Themes
text: Using example data forestploter processing way show forestploter README per code : demonstrate use based theme_oxford_forest() provide custom theme forestploter forest plot follows:
code: # Read and process example data from forestploter package  ## Read example data from forestploter package dt <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adayim/forestploter/main/inst/extdata/example_data.csv")  ## Indent the subgroup if there is a number in the placebo column dt$Subgroup <- ifelse(   is.na(dt$Placebo), dt$Subgroup, paste0("   ", dt$Subgroup) )  ## NA to blank dt$Treatment <- ifelse(is.na(dt$Treatment), "", dt$Treatment) dt$Placebo   <- ifelse(is.na(dt$Placebo), "", dt$Placebo) dt$se        <- (log(dt$hi) - log(dt$est)) / 1.96  ## Add a blank column for the forest plot to display CI. ## Adjust the column width with space.  dt$` ` <- paste(rep(" ", 20), collapse = " ")  ## Create confidence interval column to display dt$`HR (95% CI)` <- ifelse(   is.na(dt$se), "",   sprintf("%.2f (%.2f to %.2f)", dt$est, dt$low, dt$hi) ) # Create forest plot from dt and then apply theme_oxford_forest()  ## Create forest plot p <- forest(dt[ , c(1:3, 20:21)],             est = dt$est,             lower = dt$low,              upper = dt$hi,             sizes = dt$se,             ci_column = 4,             ref_line = 1,             arrow_lab = c("Placebo Better", "Treatment Better"),             xlim = c(0, 4),             ticks_at = c(0.5, 1, 2, 3),             title = "Title in Roboto plain font in Oxford blue",             footnote = "Footnote in Roboto plain font\nin Oxford royal blue",             theme = theme_oxford_forest())  ## Print plot plot(p) #> refline_lwd, refline_col will be deprecated, use refline_gp instead. #> footnote_cex, footnote_fontface, footnote_col will be deprecated, use footnote_gp instead. #> title_col, title_fontfamily will be deprecated, use title_gp instead. #> arrow_lwd, arrow_fill, arrow_col will be deprecated, use arrow_gp instead.

text: base_family Base font family set Roboto default. base_size Base font size. Default 11.5. plot_title_family Font family use plot title. Default base_family. plot_title_size Plot title text size pts. Default 16. plot_title_face Font face ("plain", "italic", "bold", "bold.italic") plot title. Default "bold". plot_title_colour Colour plot title text. Default Oxford Blue. plot_title_margin Margin bottom plot title. Default set 10. subtitle_family Font family use plot subtitle. Default "plain". subtitle_colour Colour subtitle text. Default Oxford ash grey. subtitle_margin Margin bottom plot subtitle. Default set 15. strip_text_family Font family use facet label. Default base_family. strip_text_size Facet label text size pts. Default 12. strip_text_face Font face ("plain", "italic", "bold", "bold.italic") facet label. Default "plain". caption_family Font family use caption text. Default base_family. caption_size Caption text size pts. Default 9. caption_face Font face ("plain", "italic", "bold", "bold.italic") caption text. Default "plain". caption_colour Colour caption text. Default Oxford ash grey. caption_margin Margin top plot caption text. Default set 10. axis_text_size Axis text size pts. Default base_size. axis_title_family Font family use axis title. Default subtitle_family. axis_title_size Axis title text size pts. Default 9. axis_title_colour Colour axis title text. Default Oxford ash grey. axis_title_face Font face ("plain", "italic", "bold", "bold.italic") axis title. Default "plain". axis_title_just Axis title font justification, one "bl" (bottom-left), "m" (middle), "rt" (right-top). Default "rt". legend_title_family Font family use legend title. Default subtitle_family. legend_title_colour Colour legend title text. Default Oxford ash grey. legend_text_family Font family use legend text. Default subtitle_family. legend_text_colour Colour legend text. Default Oxford ash grey. plot_margin Plot margins (specify ggplot2::margin()). plot_background_fill Fill colour plot background. Default NULL. grid_col Grid colour. Default Oxford umber. grid Panel grid. Either TRUE, FALSE, combination X (major x grid), x (minor x grid), Y (major y grid), /y (minor y grid). Default TRUE. axis_col Axis colours. Default Oxford umber. axis Add x y axes? TRUE, FALSE, "xy". Default FALSE. ticks Logical. ticks added? Default FALSE.
